":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Wellom","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Kellam  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kellam","meanings":["English: habitational name from Kelham in Nottinghamshire, so named from the dative plural of Old Norse <i>kjǫlr</i> ‘(place) at the ridges’."]}]},{"name":"Waldron","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (Mayo): from the Norman personal name <i>Waleran</i>, <i>Galeran</i> (ancient Germanic <i>Walahram</i>, Old French <i>Galeran(t)</i>), composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner’ + <i>hrafn</i> ‘raven’. Compare   Walraven  . In Ireland, where it is common, this name was Gaelicized early as <b>Mac Bhalronta</b>, also later as <b>Mac Bhaildrin</b> and <b>de Bhaldraithe</b>.","English: habitational name from a place in Sussex named Waldron. The placename derives from Old English <i>wald</i> ‘woodland’ + <i>ærn</i> ‘building’.","History: This is the name of a prominent NH family, established there since the 17th century. Richard Walderne (born <i>c.</i> 1615) came to New England from Alchester, Warwickshire, England, <i>c.</i> 1640 and settled at Dover, NH."],"variants":[{"name":"Walraven","meanings":["German and Dutch: from <i>Walravan</i>, a personal name composed of the elements <i>wal</i> ‘battlefield’ + <i>hraban</i> ‘raven’. The personal name was popular among knights and patricians of the Lower Rhine and Upper Swabian region, where the surname is still common. This surname is also found in England."]},{"name":"Waldren","meanings":["English: variant of   Waldron  ."]},{"name":"Waldrum","meanings":["English: variant of   Waldron  ."]},{"name":"Walrond","meanings":["English (Somerset and Devon): of Normin origin, a variant of   Waldron  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":65,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":74,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":109,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Waldron de Wellom was born in 1150, in Yorkshire, England as the son of Ralph de Willoughby. He had at least 1 daughter with Maud Fulletby."},"et":{"1150–":"1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1147–Female":"1147–Surnud","1170–1200":"1170–1200","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","1224":"1224","1147":"1147","1200":"1200","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Wellum, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Knaresborough Castle, Yorkshire, England":"Knaresborough, Yorkshire, 